English: What would a hacker for hire want us for?
Chinese: 便利店的駭客，找我有什麼事？
German: Was sollte denn ein Auftragshacker von uns wollen?

English:
I don't know anyone like that. And you've just
barged into our team. I ought to charge you an
admission fee!
Chinese:
才不知道那樣子的傢伙咧。
……比起這些，別的隊伍擅自闖進來，
至少給我付一下入場費啊！
Korean:
그런 녀석은 몰라.
…것보다 다른 팀이 무단으로 들어왔어.
입장료 정도는 내고 가라고!
German:
So jemanden kenne ich nicht. Und du bist einfach
in unser Team geplatzt. Ich sollte dir Eintritt
berechnen!

English: You're not worth my time. Get out of my sight.
Chinese:
……你這傢伙不配我動手，
還不趕快給我消失。
German: Du bist meine Zeit nicht wert. Scher dich weg.

English:
This is Nakano Stripes territory. No boys allowed!
Leave at once!
Chinese:
這裡是我們「中野條紋」的領域。
禁止男生出現，快點出去吧！
Korean:
여긴 우리 「나카노 스트라이프스」의 구역이야.
남자 금지니까 얼른 나가라구!
German:
Dies ist das Gebiet der Nakano Stripes. Jungs
haben hier nichts zu suchen! Hau sofort ab!
